--cleanup tier1      Remove tmp/ and raw .mif intermediates only
                     Frees the most space with least risk
                     Safe to run while pipeline is still processing
                     other subjects

--cleanup tier2      tier1 + eddy/bias/registration intermediates
                     Keeps dwi_final.* and all outputs intact
                     Good default after QC passes

--cleanup tier3      tier2 + raw tractograms (keeps SIFT-filtered only)
                     Only safe after connectomes are confirmed good

--cleanup all        Everything in DIR_WORK except checkpoints
                     Nuclear option — reprocessing requires full rerun